# AREA: build · DEPLOY
# Build context exclusions for `docker build` against worker/Dockerfile.
# The COPY worker/ line in that Dockerfile is intentionally broad
# (other families' source comes along) so the in-image `models` package
# stays consistent with dev — but per-family .venv directories and
# bytecode caches must not bleed into the image. They're large (GBs of
# torch/mlx wheels) and cache-bust on unrelated edits.

# Per-family virtual envs — built locally for development, not for
# container deployment.
worker/models/*/.venv/
worker/.venv/

# Python bytecode caches.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/

# Tauri shell & Go server are unrelated to the worker image.
app/
server/

# Repo metadata not needed inside the image.
.git/
.github/
.claude/
